<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB06095</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT INCREASING THE AMOUNT OF AUTHORIZED ELECTION CAMPAIGN EXPENSES OF CANDIDATES AND POLITICAL PARTIES, AMENDING FOR THE PURPOSE SECTION 13 OF REPUBLIC ACT NO.7166, ENTITLED, "AN ACT PROVIDING FOR SYNCHRONIZED NATIONAL AND LOCAL ELECTIONS AND FOR ELECTORAL REFORMS, AUTHORIZING APPROPRIATIONS THEREFOR, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES"</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE :  Increasing The Amount Of Authorized Election Campaign Expenses Of Candidates And Political Parties</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to update the authorized expenses of candidates and political parties as follows: 1.For Candidates: Fifty Pesos (P50.00) for President, Vice-President and Senators; Thirty Pesos (P30.00) for other candidates for every voter currently registered in the constituency where they are seeking to be elected and have filed a certificate of candidacy for 2. For political parties: Fifty Pesos (P50.00) for their respective national candidates; and Thirty Pesos (P30.00) for local candidates for every voter.
Mandates the Commission on Elections, in consultation with the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas, the NEDA and the PSA to adjust the amounts of authorized election campaign expenses every six years based on the inflation rate and the consumer price index. </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>FORTUNO, JOCELYN F., CHIPECO, JOAQUIN JR. M., AGABAS, TYRONE D., OAMINAL, HENRY S., SILVERIO, LORNA C., VILLANUEVA, NOEL L., PIMENTEL, JOHNNY TY, FERRER, JULIET MARIE DE LEON, SAVELLANO, DEOGRACIAS VICTOR &quot;DV&quot; B., ROMUALDO, XAVIER JESUS D., NIETO, JOHN MARVIN &quot;YUL SERVO&quot; C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2020-01-29</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Romualdez (F.M.) (000 2020-03-10)</td><td>2. Cagas (000 2020-05-31)</td><tr><td colspan=3>AUTHORS(Final/Third Reading) :</td></tr><tr><td width='%33'>1. Fortuno</td><td width='33%'>2. Chipeco</td><tr><td width='%33'>3. Agabas</td><td width='33%'>4. Oaminal</td><tr><td width='%33'>5. Silverio</td><td width='33%'>6. Villanueva (N.)</td><tr><td width='%33'>7. Pimentel</td><td width='33%'>8. Ferrer (J.M.)</td><tr><td width='%33'>9. Savellano</td><td width='33%'>10. Romualdo</td><tr><td width='%33'>11. Nieto</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITTEE REPORT NO.&nbsp00208</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBMITTED ON 2020-01-29</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBMITTED BY:&nbspSUFFRAGE AND ELECTORAL REFORMS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>RECOMMENDATIONS:&nbspApproval in substitution of House Bills Numbered 1318, 1479, 3731, 3838, 4091, 4191 and 5187</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBSTITUTED BILLS:&nbspHB01318, HB01479, HB03731, HB03838, HB04091, HB04191, HB05187</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON RULES ON 2020-01-29</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE INCLUDED IN OB:&nbsp2020-01-29<